David Ortiz, Prince Fielder Will Lead MLB All-Star Home Run Derby Teams

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-07-06T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/davd-ortiz-prince-fielder-named-to-lead-mlb-all-star-home-run-derby-teams.html
David Ortiz  of the  Boston Red Sox  and
Prince Fielder of the Milwaukee Brewers were named captains of
 Major League Baseball ’s All-Star home-run derby teams.  Ortiz, the winner of the 2010 derby, selected his teammate,
first baseman Adrian Gonzalez; Jose Bautista of the  Toronto Blue
Jays ; and New York Yankees second baseman Robinson Cano for the
American League team.  Fielder, who won the derby in 2009, picked his teammate,
second baseman Rickie Weeks; St. Louis Cardinals outfielder Matt Holliday; and Los Angeles Dodgers outfielder Matt Kemp for the
National League lineup.  The Home Run Derby will be held July 11, the night before
the All-Star Game at Chase Field in Phoenix.  State Farm Insurance and the league will donate $18,000 for
every home run hit with a gold ball. State Farm will give $3,000
to the Boys & Girls Club of America for every non-gold ball hit.  The winning captain’s charity will receive $150,000,
$100,000 will go to the Boys & Girls Club in the name of the
winning captain and $25,000 will be awarded to the losing
captain’s charity.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  